      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly hurtful to feel that your humanity is reduced to data points when your contributions are viewed through a corporate lens like Slack channels. Many people genuinely struggle with this sense of invisibility, but it is true that behind every profile and resume is a complex individual with fears, joys, and unique stories. While system efficiency often blinds leaders to the human beneath the head of State, small acts of genuine recognition usually ripple out to validate those feelings. You aren't nothing; your presence matters even when the algorithm tries to forget it.",
