      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Walking away might feel like a relief initially, but actively ignoring the people who rely on you can make the silence in your home feel louder and more overwhelming over time. It is a profound cycle where we retreat into digital roles to protect ourselves, only to wonder if anyone notices when we finally disconnect. There is no logical reason to force yourself to remain a ghost, but there is also difficult talk to have about safety before choosing the path of leaving. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional who can help navigate these heavy thoughts without the weight of having to \"perform\" yet again.",
